Reasoning: The paper deals with the characterization of the Finite Transmission Feedback Information (FTFI) capacity for channels with memory, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The methodology utilized in the paper involves stochastic optimal control theory, which is a subfield of control systems (cs.SY). The paper also utilizes variational equalities, which is a topic in optimization and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of channel distributions and transmission cost functions, which can be considered as topics in mathematical analysis (cs.MA) and data structures (cs.DS), respectively.
